{"declarations":[{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Probability/Notation.html#ProbabilityTheory.termℙ\"><span class=\"name\">ProbabilityTheory</span>.<span class=\"name\">termℙ</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.ParserDescr\">Lean.ParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"`ℙ` is a notation for `volume` on a measured space. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Probability/Notation.html#ProbabilityTheory.termℙ","kind":"def","line":71,"name":"ProbabilityTheory.termℙ","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Probability/Notation.lean#L71-L72"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Probability/Notation.html#ProbabilityTheory.«term∂_/∂_»\"><span class=\"name\">ProbabilityTheory</span>.<span class=\"name\">«term∂_/∂_»</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.ParserDescr\">Lean.ParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"`∂P/∂Q` is the Radon–Nikodym derivative of `P` with respect to `Q`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Probability/Notation.html#ProbabilityTheory.«term∂_/∂_»","kind":"def","line":68,"name":"ProbabilityTheory.«term∂_/∂_»","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Probability/Notation.lean#L68-L69"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Probability/Notation.html#ProbabilityTheory.«term_≤ₐₛ_»\"><span class=\"name\">ProbabilityTheory</span>.<span class=\"name\">«term_≤ₐₛ_»</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.TrailingParserDescr\">Lean.TrailingParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"`X ≤ₐₛ Y` if `X ≤ Y` almost surely. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Probability/Notation.html#ProbabilityTheory.«term_≤ₐₛ_»","kind":"def","line":65,"name":"ProbabilityTheory.«term_≤ₐₛ_»","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Probability/Notation.lean#L65-L66"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Probability/Notation.html#ProbabilityTheory.«term_=ₐₛ_»\"><span class=\"name\">ProbabilityTheory</span>.<span class=\"name\">«term_=ₐₛ_»</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.TrailingParserDescr\">Lean.TrailingParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"`X =ₐₛ Y` if `X = Y` almost surely. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Probability/Notation.html#ProbabilityTheory.«term_=ₐₛ_»","kind":"def","line":62,"name":"ProbabilityTheory.«term_=ₐₛ_»","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Probability/Notation.lean#L62-L63"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Probability/Notation.html#ProbabilityTheory.«term_⟦_|_⟧»\"><span class=\"name\">ProbabilityTheory</span>.<span class=\"name\">«term_⟦_|_⟧»</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.TrailingParserDescr\">Lean.TrailingParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"`P⟦s | m⟧` is the conditional expectation of `s` with respect to `m` under measure `P`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Probability/Notation.html#ProbabilityTheory.«term_⟦_|_⟧»","kind":"def","line":58,"name":"ProbabilityTheory.«term_⟦_|_⟧»","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Probability/Notation.lean#L58-L60"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Probability/Notation.html#ProbabilityTheory.«term𝔼[_]»\"><span class=\"name\">ProbabilityTheory</span>.<span class=\"name\">«term𝔼[_]»</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.ParserDescr\">Lean.ParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"`𝔼[X]` is the expectation of `X`, defined as its Lebesgue integral. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Probability/Notation.html#ProbabilityTheory.«term𝔼[_]»","kind":"def","line":55,"name":"ProbabilityTheory.«term𝔼[_]»","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Probability/Notation.lean#L55-L56"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Probability/Notation.html#ProbabilityTheory.«term__[_]»\"><span class=\"name\">ProbabilityTheory</span>.<span class=\"name\">«term__[_]»</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.TrailingParserDescr\">Lean.TrailingParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"`P[X]` is the expectation of `X` under the measure `P`.\n\nNote that this notation can conflict with the `GetElem` notation for lists. Usually if you see an\nerror about ambiguous notation when trying to write `l[i]` for a list, it means that Lean could\nnot find `i < l.length`, and so fell back to trying this notation as well. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Probability/Notation.html#ProbabilityTheory.«term__[_]»","kind":"def","line":52,"name":"ProbabilityTheory.«term__[_]»","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Probability/Notation.lean#L52-L52"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Probability/Notation.html#ProbabilityTheory.«term𝔼[_|_]»\"><span class=\"name\">ProbabilityTheory</span>.<span class=\"name\">«term𝔼[_|_]»</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.ParserDescr\">Lean.ParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"`𝔼[f | m]` is the conditional expectation of `f` with respect to `m`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Probability/Notation.html#ProbabilityTheory.«term𝔼[_|_]»","kind":"def","line":41,"name":"ProbabilityTheory.«term𝔼[_|_]»","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Probability/Notation.lean#L41-L43"}}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.MeasureTheory.Function.ConditionalExpectation.Basic","Mathlib.MeasureTheory.Measure.Decomposition.Lebesgue"],"instances":[],"name":"Mathlib.Probability.Notation"}